# MongoDB Connection String
# Copy this file to .Renviron and fill in your actual connection string
# DO NOT commit .Renviron to git - it contains secrets!
#
# Get your connection string from MongoDB Atlas:
# 1. Go to your cluster in Atlas
# 2. Click "Connect" > "Drivers"
# 3. Copy the connection string and replace <password> with your actual password

MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://your_username:your_password@your-cluster.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=your-app

# Python Configuration (Optional - improves matching speed)
# ============================================================================
# The app uses rapidfuzz (Python) for faster fuzzy string matching.
# This is optional - the app works fine with R-only matching.
#
# To enable rapidfuzz:
# 1. Install Python 3.8+ on your system
# 2. Run: pip install rapidfuzz
# 3. Optionally set RETICULATE_PYTHON below if R can't find Python
#
# Uncomment and set to your Python path if needed:
# RETICULATE_PYTHON=/usr/bin/python3
# RETICULATE_PYTHON=C:/Python311/python.exe
# RETICULATE_PYTHON=~/miniconda3/envs/mapper/bin/python
